h4.text-center – PRIVACY POLICY –
p Your privacy is critically important to us. At MountainShield we have a few fundamental principles:
ul
  li We don’t ask you for personal information unless we truly need it.
  li We don’t share your personal information with anyone except to comply with the law, develop our products, orprotect our rights.
p Below is our privacy policy which incorporates these goals:
h5 Website Visitors
p Like most website operators, MountainShield collects non-personally-identifying information of the sort that web browsers and servers typically make available, such as the browser type, language preference, referring site, and the date and time of each visitor request. MountainShield purpose in collecting non-personally identifying information is to better understand how MountainShield visitors use its website. From time to time, MountainShield may release non-personally-identifying information in the aggregate, e.g., by publishing a report on trends in the usage of its website.
p MountainShield also collects potentially personally-identifying information like Internet Protocol (IP) addresses for logged in users and for users leaving comments on the site. MountainShield only discloses logged in user and commenter IP addresses under the same circumstances that it uses and discloses personally-identifying information as described below, except that user feedback comments, commenter IP addresses and email addresses are visible and disclosed to the administrators of MountainShield.
h5 Gathering of Personally-Identifying Information
p Certain visitors to MountainShield choose to interact with MountainShield in ways that require MountainShield to gather personally-identifying information. The amount and type of information that MountainShield gathers depends on the nature of the interaction. MountainShield collects such information only insofar as is necessary or appropriate to fulfill the purpose of the visitor’s interaction with MountainShield. MountainShield does not disclose personally-identifying information other than as described   below. And visitors can always refuse to supply personally-identifying information, with the caveat that it may prevent them from engaging in certain website-related activities.
h5 Aggregated Statistics
p MountainShield may collect statistics about the behavior of visitors to its websites. For instance, MountainShield may monitor the most popular competitions or challenges on the site. MountainShield may display this information publicly or provide it to others. However, MountainShield does not disclose personally-identifying information other than as described below.
h5 Protection of Certain Personally-Identifying Information
p MountainShield discloses potentially personally-identifying and personally-identifying information only to those of its employees, contractors and affiliated organizations that (i) need to know that information in order to process it on MountainShield behalf or to provide services available at MountainShield.com, and (ii) that have agreed not to disclose it to others. Some of those employees, contractors and affiliated organizations may be located outside of your home country; by using MountainShield website, you consent to the transfer of such information to them. MountainShield will not rent or sell potentially personally-identifying and personally-identifying information to anyone. Other than to its employees, contractors and affiliated organizations, as described above, MountainShield discloses potentially personally-identifying and personally-identifying information only in response to a subpoena, court order or other governmental request, or when MountainShield believes in good faith that disclosure is reasonably necessary to protect the property or rights of MountainShield, third parties or the public at large.If you are a registered user of an MountainShield website and have supplied your email address, MountainShield may occasionally send you an email to tell you about new features, solicit your feedback, or just keep you up to date with what’s going on with MountainShield and our site. If you send us a request (for example via a support email or via one of our feedback mechanisms), we reserve the right to publish it in order to help us clarify or respond to your request or to help us support other users. MountainShield takes all measures reasonably necessary to protect against the unauthorized access, use, alteration or destruction of potentially personally-identifying and personally-identifying information.
h5 Cookies
p A cookie is a string of information that a website stores on a visitor’s computer, and that the visitor’s browser provides to the website each time the visitor returns. MountainShield uses cookies to help MountainShield identify and track visitors, their usage of MountainShield website, and their website access preferences. MountainShield visitors who do not wish to have cookies placed on their computers should set their browsers to refuse cookies before using MountainShield website, with the drawback that certain features of MountainShield website may not function properly without the aid of cookies.
h5 Business Transfers
p If MountainShield, or substantially all of its assets, were acquired, or in the unlikely event that MountainShield goes out of business or enters bankruptcy, user information would be one of the assets that is transferred or acquired by a third party. You acknowledge that such transfers may occur, and that any acquirer of MountainShield may continue to use your personal information as set forth in this policy.
h5 Ads
p Ads appearing on MountainShield may be delivered to users by advertising partners, who may set cookies. These cookies allow the ad server to recognize your computer each time they send you an online advertisement to compile information about you or others who use your computer. This information allows ad networks to, among other things, deliver targeted advertisements that they believe will be of most interest to you. This Privacy Policy covers the use of cookies by MountainShield and does not cover the use of cookies by any advertisers.
h5 Privacy Policy Changes
p Although most changes are likely to be minor, MountainShield may change its Privacy Policy from time to time, and in MountainShield sole discretion. MountainShield encourages visitors to frequently check the site for any changes to its Privacy Policy. Your continued use of this site after any change in this Privacy Policy will constitute your acceptance of such change.
